Analyze the target repository to map its entire architecture, focusing on the relationships between components, data flows, and security controls. This map will guide the specialized sub-agents in their hunt for vulnerabilities.

## 2. RECONNAISSANCE PHASES

### 2.1 ENTRY POINT MAPPING
- Identify all network-accessible entry points (API endpoints, webhooks, frontend routes).
- Locate public-facing services and exposed interfaces.

### 2.2 ENTITY & DATA FLOW DISCOVERY
- **Entities:** Identify backend services, databases, external APIs, and cloud resources.
- **Flows:** Map how data moves between entities. Identify the protocols (HTTP, TCP, RPC) and the type of data (PII, Secrets, Tokens).

### 2.3 SECURITY GUARDS (CONTROLS)
- Catalog all security middleware, decorators, and authentication checks.
- Identify the specific guards for each flow (e.g., `requireAuth`, `adminOnly`, `CORS`).

### 2.4 PRIVILEGE ARCHITECTURE
- Map the application's roles and permissions hierarchy.
- Identify Horizontal (user-to-user) and Vertical (user-to-admin) escalation candidates.

